==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Embay
<hw>Em*bay"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>em-</ets> + <ets>bay</ets> to bathe.]</ety> <def>To bathe; to
soothe or lull as by bathing.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Embay</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Embay
<hw>Em*bay"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Embayed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Embaying</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref. <ets>em-</ets> + 1st
<ets>bay</ets>.]</ety> <def>To shut in, or shelter, as in a
bay.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If that the Turkish fleet⟦br⟧
Be not ensheltered and <qex>embayed</qex>, they are drowned.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Embayment</ent>⟦br⟧
